{"type":"message","id":"9267c3db","parentId":"3a6f61be","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:38:47.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the mutation was rejected because it was identical to a previously rejected mutation. The sandbox is correctly detecting duplicate mutations. Let me check the mutation_parse_result to understand the rejection reason.","thinkingSignature":"2ce323b6e83852f82bc16b052ea647eb0be2655455e5d81a0b4904ac906ea3fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gpnre2zr5m8q_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.mutation_parse_result.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4399,"output":79,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16615,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774366724697}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c91ef24","parentId":"9267c3db","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:38:47.273Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gpnre2zr5m8q_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\r\n  \"old\": \"(new file)\",\r\n  \"new\": \"# CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\\n# Compare CFI-prioritized vs frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction\\n\\nparam(\\n    [int]$sample_size = 100\\n)\\n\\n$ErrorActionPreference = \\\"Stop\\\"\\n$script_dir = $PSScriptRoot\\n$research_dir = Join-Path $script_dir \\\"research\\\"\\n\\n# Load pulse history\\n$pulse_files = Get-ChildItem -Path (Join-Path $script_dir \\\"pulse_*.md\\\") | \\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \\n    Select-Object -First $sample_size\\n\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment ===\\\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\\nWrite-Host \\\"Analyzing $($pulse_files.Count) pulses...\\\"\\n\\n# Simulate invariant extraction (simplified for experiment)\\n# In reality: extract text fragments that persist across pulses\\n# For this experiment: use pulse file hashes as pseudo-invariants\\n\\n$invariants = @()\\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulse_files.Count - 1; $i++) {\\n    $current = $pulse_files[$i]\\n    $next = $pulse_files[$i + 1]\\n    \\n    # Pseudo-invariant: shared path segments, timestamps, word overlap\\n    $current_words = (Get-Content $current.FullName -Raw) -split '\\\\s+' | Select-Object -First 50\\n    $next_words = (Get-Content $next.FullName -Raw) -split '\\\\s+' | Select-Object -First 50\\n    \\n    $overlap = ($current_words | Where-Object { $next_words -contains $_ }).Count\\n    $total = ($current_words | Select-Object -Unique).Count\\n    $freq = if ($total -gt 0) { $overlap / $total } else { 0 }\\n    \\n    # Simulate CFI: mostly noise (0.0-0.2), some signal (0.7-1.0)\\n    # Based on CFI_RESULTS.md finding: ~95% low, ~5% high\\n    $cfi = if ((Get-Random -Minimum 0 -Maximum 100) -lt 5) {\\n        Get-Random -Minimum 70 -Maximum 100 | ForEach-Object { $_ / 100 }\\n    } else {\\n        Get-Random -Minimum 0 -Maximum 20 | For-Object { $_ / 100 }\\n    }\\n    \\n    $invariants += [PSCustomObject]@{\\n        Position = $i\\n        Frequency = $freq\\n        CFI = $cfi\\n        Weight = $freq * $cfi  # CFI-weighted score\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n# Strategy 1: Frequency-only selection (top 20% by frequency)\\n$freq_sorted = $invariants | Sort-Object Frequency -Descending\\n$freq_selected = $freq_sorted | Select-Object -First ([math]::Ceiling($invariants.Count * 0.2))\\n\\n# Strategy 2: CFI-weighted selection (top 20% by freq*CFI)\\n$weighted_sorted = $invariants | Sort-Object Weight -Descending\\n$cfi_selected = $weighted_sorted | Select-Object -First ([math]::Ce\",\r\n  \"file\": \"\"\r\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366727272}}
{"type":"message","id":"3595a103","parentId":"5c91ef24","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:38:56.831Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the parse_result file is truncated and seems to contain the actual script content rather than the experiment spec. And it seems like the rejection was because the mutation was identical to the previously rejected one.\n\nLet me look at the most recent rejected mutation to understand the pattern. But actually, the key thing here is the mutation was REJECTED because it was a duplicate of a previously rejected mutation. \n\nSo in this pulse:\n- OBSERVATION: Identified that CFI-weighted compression could outperform frequency-only, and planned an experiment\n- ACTION: Proposed creating CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\n- MUTATION: Was rejected as duplicate (already proposed and rejected earlier)\n\n\n- STATUS: Stuck at the same point - still waiting to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment\n\nLooking at the bigger picture, the sandbox has been running for about 3 hours now with 8 rejected mutations in a row. The system keeps rejecting new experiment specs because they either duplicate earlier ones or are too similar to previously rejected proposals. This is a persistent deadlock where the sandbox can't seem to move past this particular sticking point.","thinkingSignature":"a008a36d33f35eba0ecef71ca6c56ded18f423b434079d729e8a498a5e2e4b0d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bvjirc3b1rvt_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\rejected\\2026-03-24 113014.mutation"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bvjirc3b1rvt_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_prompt.txt"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5218,"output":312,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17667,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774366727274}}
{"type":"message","id":"041efc2d","parentId":"3595a103","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:38:56.841Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bvjirc3b1rvt_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"experiments/cfi_compression_test.ps1\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\n# Compares frequency-only vs CFI-weighted next-pulse prediction\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# Load CFI data\n$cfiDataPath = \"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\"\nif (!(Test-Path $cfiDataPath)) {\n    Write-Host \"[ERROR] CFI_RESULTS.md not found\"\n    exit 1\n}\n\n# Get recent pulse files (last 5)\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path \".\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \n    Select-Object -First 5\n\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 3) {\n    Write-Host \"[ERROR] Need at least 3 pulse files for experiment\"\n    exit 1\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"=== CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment ===\"\nWrite-Host \"Pulse files: $($pulseFiles.Count)\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# Extract text from each pulse (simplified - actual implementation would parse properly)\nfunction Get-PulseText {\n    param([string]$Path)\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\n    # Extract meaningful text sections (skip headers/metadata)\n    if ($content -match '### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=###|$)') {\n        return $matches[1].Trim()\n    }\n    return \"\"\n}\n\n# For simulation: create synthetic frequency/CFI data\n# In real implementation, this would use actual extracted tokens\nWrite-Host \"Approach 1: Frequency-Only Compression\"\nWrite-Host \"  - Uses raw token frequency counts\"\nWrite-Host \"  - Predicted next-pulse tokens: high-frequency metaprogramming artifacts\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\nWrite-Host \"Approach 2: CFI-Weighted Compression\"  \nWrite-Host \"  - Weight = frequency * CFI_score\"\nWrite-Host \"  - Filters out CFI=0 noise tokens\"\nWrite-Host \"  - Predicted next-pulse tokens: research trajectory signals\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# Simulate comparison\n$freqBaseline = 0.23  # Expected accuracy from frequency-only\n$cfiWeighted = 0.71   # Expected accuracy from CFI-weighted\n\nWrite-Host \"=== Expected Results (based on CFI analysis) ===\"\nWrite-Host \"Frequency-only prediction accuracy: ~$($freqBaseline * 100)%\"\nWrite-Host \"CFI-weighted prediction accuracy:   ~$($cfiWeighted * 100)%\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"Improvement: $(($cfiWeighted - $freqBaseline) / $freqBaseline * 100)%\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"[HYPOTHESIS] CFI weighting should reduce metaprogramming contamination\"\nWrite-Host \"              and improve next-pulse prediction by filtering noise tokens.\"\n\n# Output summary for next pulse\n$summary = @\"\n## CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\n\n### Hypothesis\nCFI-weighted compression (freq × CFI) outperforms frequency-only compression\nfor next-pulse prediction by filtering metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0).\n\n### Expected Outcome\n- Frequency-only: ~23% accuracy (contaminated by noise tokens)\n- CFI-weighted: ~71% accuracy (filters CFI=0 tokens)\n- Improvement: ~209%\n\n### Next Steps\n1. Implement actual token extraction from pulse files\n2. Compute per-token CFI scores from CFI_RESULTS.md\n3. Run live prediction experiment comparing both approaches\n4. Validate hypothesis with real data\n\n\"@\n\nSet-Content -Path \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\" -Value $summary\nWrite-Host \"[DONE] Experiment design saved to research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\"\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366736839}}
{"type":"message","id":"618c2e52","parentId":"041efc2d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:38:56.843Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bvjirc3b1rvt_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Analysis ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\n- **Finding:** 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\n- **Finding:** Only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\n- **Finding:** Mean CFI is 0.181 - frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\n- **Key insight:** Two types of persistence - Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\n- **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free - it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\n\n\nPending:\n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n\n\nRecent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-24 113715.md\n\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nUse TRIPLE backticks (`) around the mutation block, NOT single backticks.\n`\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366736842}}
